# Tightrope Walker

Over-under intervals that dance around your threshold. You alternate between just below and just above FTP, forcing your body to clear lactate while riding hard. This is where race fitness is forged.

- 10:00 45%
  - :30 Easy warmup
  - 5:00 Get the legs ready — these intervals are sneaky hard
  - 3:00 Over-unders start in 2 minutes
  - :30 The "under" should feel sustainable, the "over" should burn
- 5x
  - 2:00 92%
    - :05 Under — steady, controlled, just below threshold
    - 1:00 Hold this effort, stay relaxed
  - 1:00 108%
    - :05 OVER — push into the red, embrace the burn
    - :30 Hold it, don't back off
  - 2:00 92%
    - :05 Back under — recover while still riding hard
    - 1:00 Clear that lactate, stay smooth
  - 1:00 108%
    - :05 Over again — this one's harder, that's the point
    - :30 Almost through it
  - 2:00 50%
    - :10 Full recovery — breathe deep
    - 1:00 Next set in 1 minute
- 10:00 40%
  - :10 All 5 sets done — that's serious threshold work
  - 5:00 Spin it out easy, you earned this cooldown
